<h2>Step 1: Keyword Research for Shopify Stores</h2>

<p>
Your products must target what customers are searching for.
</p>

<p>
Instead of:
</p>

<ul>
<li>“Phone case”</li>
</ul>

<p>
Use:
</p>

<ul>
<li>“buy durable phone case online Kenya”</li>
<li>“affordable iPhone case Nairobi delivery”</li>
<li>“best protective phone case for drops Kenya”</li>
</ul>

<p>
These are <strong>long-tail keywords with high buying intent</strong>.
</p>

---

<h2>Step 2: Optimize Product Pages</h2>

<p>
Every product page should include:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Keyword-rich product titles</li>
<li>SEO descriptions</li>
<li>High-quality images</li>
<li>Internal links</li>
</ul>

<p>
Example:
</p>

<p>
Instead of: “Yoga Pants”  
Use:  
<strong>“High-Waist Yoga Pants for Women – Comfortable Gym Wear in Kenya”</strong>
</p>

---

<h2>Step 3: Improve Shopify Store Structure</h2>

<p>
Your store must be easy to navigate.
</p>

<p>
Structure should include:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Collections (categories)</li>
<li>Clear menu navigation</li>
<li>Internal linking</li>
</ul>

<p>
Poor structure = poor rankings.
</p>

---

